[center][size=6][color=#ffff00][b]Clothing Sets Checklist: Locations Guide[/b][/color][/size]
[size=4]Every location, requirement, and walking direction from the in-game checklist, in one written record.[/size][/center]

This is a companion article to the [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/cyberpunk2077/mods/26829][b]Clothing Sets Checklist[/b][/url] mod. Every entry below is generated from the same data the in-game UI uses, so it stays consistent with what the mod tells you. Use it as a written reference if you do not have Cyber Engine Tweaks installed, can't install mods (console), or just prefer reading.

If you spot anything inaccurate, please leave a comment on the mod page so I can fix both the article and the in-game database.

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]How to read this guide[/b][/color][/size]
[list]
[*]Each set is in a collapsible spoiler. Click the set name to expand it.
[*]Items include the nearest fast travel point, district, any requirement, and walking directions.
[*]Where an entry has a short summary and detailed steps, the summary is the first line and the detailed steps follow.
[*]Life path starting outfits and ending epilogue clothing are intentionally excluded.
[/list]

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Set Index[/b][/color][/size]
[list]
[*]Badge
[*]Corporate
[*]Fixer
[*]Media
[*]Netrunner
[*]Nomad
[*]Rocker
[*]Solo
[*]Techie
[*]V's Set
[*]Yorinobu
[*]Silverhand
[*]Patch Quests
[*]MaxTac
[*]NUS Infiltrator
[*]GOG
[/list]

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Badge[/b][/color][/size]
[spoiler]
[size=4][b]Holo-tinted badge goggles[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Northside Apartment
[b]Location:[/b] Watson, Northside
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a deceased cop behind the Northside apartment.

From the Northside Apartment fast travel terminal, head west along the street and cross the Goldsmith and Martin intersection turning right and follow the road until you reach a small alley on the left. Head down the alley until you get to the open space, there should be an area with an NCPD squad car on your left.
The body is next to the car.

[size=4][b]Heavy-duty aramid-reinforced badge coat[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Almuneca & Jerez
[b]Location:[/b] Santo Domingo, Rancho Coronado
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted off a corpse at what appears to be a failed attempt to apprehend a criminal at a house near the southern edge of Rancho Coronado.

Facing the Almuneca & Jerez fast travel terminal, look West North West. You should see a NCPD SUV. Head towards it.
The body is next to the furthest NCPD squad car.

[size=4][b]Anti-puncture neotac pants with composite lining[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Metro: Farrier & Ferguson
[b]Location:[/b] Watson, Little China
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a deceased cop in a recessed walkway near a side road on the northwest side of Little China.

From the metro, head west until you see a blue neon 24 arrow pointing to the location with the body.
Just look for the blood.

[size=4][b]Waterproof badge combat boots[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Woodhaven Street
[b]Location:[/b] Santo Domingo, Rancho Coronado
[b]Directions:[/b]
You can loot two pairs of boots from a couple of formerly living NCPD Badges near a pile of garbage at the base of the Petrochem Dam.

From the Woodhaven Street fast travel terminal, head west until see 3 sets of stairs leading up. At the top of the 3rd set you'll see a building with a pinky-purple door right in front of you.
The bodies are on the roof.
[/spoiler]

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Corporate[/b][/color][/size]
[spoiler]
[size=4][b]Tactical hybrid-glass corporate glasses[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Rancho Coronado East
[b]Location:[/b] Santo Domingo, Rancho Coronado
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a metal chest at a billboard near a bend in the road.

From Rancho Coronado East fast travel, head south-west along the winding road leading up and away from Rancho Coronado.
Look for the billboard structure near the northernmost bend.

[size=4][b]Corporate blazer with bulletproof lining[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Offshore St
[b]Location:[/b] Watson, Northside
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a corpse next to a burning car and a closed diner.

From the Offshore St Fast travel head north east across the train tracks and turn left. Follow the road until you get to an intersection and turn right. Keep following that road until you get to a building with a 'Barely Illegal' sign out the front on your right.
The body is next to the burning car nearby.

[size=4][b]Carbonweave silk corporate shirt[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Corporation St
[b]Location:[/b] City Center, Downtown
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a body behind scaffolding in a back alley.

From Corporation St fast travel, cross the road and head east until you get to a construction site on your right.
Go under the scaffolding to find the body.

[size=4][b]Breathable reinforced bio-cotton corporate slacks[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Oil Fields
[b]Location:[/b] Watson, Northside
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a corpse next to a burning car and a Trauma Team AV.

From the Oil Fields fast travel, follow the road  south-west and turn left at the intersection. Cross the bridge and turn left at the next intersection Head towards the building on your left. You will see a Trauma Team AV and a burning car in the parking lot.
The body is next to the burning car.

[size=4][b]Ergonomic reinforced corporate pumps/evening shoes[/b][/size]
[b]Requirement:[/b] Complete 'I fought the Law' side job
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Sam Amaro St
[b]Location:[/b] Westbrook, Charter Hill
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a body between burning vans.

From Sam Amaro St fast travel, head north across the bridge and turn left, then immediately take the next right. Enter the parking lot of the large building past the boom gates.
The body to the right near the burning vans.
[/spoiler]

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Fixer[/b][/color][/size]
[spoiler]
[size=4][b]Polycarbonate opti-enhanced fixer glasses[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Rancho Coronado South
[b]Location:[/b] Santo Domingo, Arroyo
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a dead body in an alley.

From the Rancho Coronado South fast travel, head south-west. Look for an industrial site full of containers and a big crane at the end of the T-intersection.
The body is behind the blue shipping containers.

[size=4][b]Trilayer aramid-weave fixer skirt with jacket/coat[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Kendal Park
[b]Location:[/b] Santo Domingo, Rancho Coronado
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a box in the middle of the destroyed 'Ferris wheel' area.

From Kendal Park fast travel, head to the destroyed Ferris wheel.
The box is right in front of one of the capsules.

[size=4][b]Heat-resistant aramid-weave fixer bustier/shirt[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Ebunike metro station
[b]Location:[/b] Heywood, The Glen
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a corpse in a back alley.

From Ebunike metro station, turn right and follow the road south. Take a left at the intersection onto the one way street. There is a green metal wall with Valentino's graffiti next to a Buck-A-Slice on your right at the corner of Haakenson and Piper. Jump over the wall to the other side.
If you don't have double jump yet, you can use the nearby vendor tent to jump over the fence.

[size=4][b]Protective-layer fixer skirt/pants[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Jig-jig Street
[b]Location:[/b] Westbrook, Japantown
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a small hut on the roof of a building.

From the fast travel terminal, face the Jig-Jig Street purple sign. Look up to your left and climb up until you reach a metal shack on the roof of that building.
The item is inside the shack.

[size=4][b]Elastiweave fixer pumps with reinforced seams/shoes[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Crescent & Broad St
[b]Location:[/b] Westbrook, Japantown
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a dead man's body in a blue crashed van (he is the driver).

Face the Crescent & Broad St fast travel terminal and look left. There is a ramp leading to an underground garage.
The blue van is on the ramp.
[/spoiler]

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Media[/b][/color][/size]
[spoiler]
[size=4][b]Media baseball cap with reactive layer[/b][/size]
[b]Requirement:[/b] Complete 'Life During Wartime' quest
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Regional Airport
[b]Location:[/b] Badlands, Jackson Plains
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from the top of a metal tower.

From Regional Airport fast travel, head to the metal tower in the middle of the abandoned airport.
You can walk on the metal beams or double-jump up onto the platform.

[size=4][b]Armored media ocuset with camera[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Regional Airport
[b]Location:[/b] Badlands, Jackson Plains
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a container inside an abandoned RV.

From Regional Airport fast travel, head west-south-west. The RV is parked near a big antenna thingy.
The container is on your left as you enter.

[size=4][b]Laminate-armor media ballistic vest[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Crescent & Broad St
[b]Location:[/b] Westbrook, Japantown
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a dead body on a balcony.

Face the Crescent & Broad St fast travel terminal, turn right and diagonally cross intersection. Take a right turn again and enter the alley with the Xiao Xiongmao restaurant. Climb the stairs at the end of the alley. Look at the building on the right with the balconies.
The body is behind the sheet on the lowest balcony

[size=4][b]Heat-resistant nanoweave media shirt[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Corporation St
[b]Location:[/b] Heywood, Wellsprings
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from under the street jutting out into the water.

From Corporation St fast travel, look for the street extending over the water and follow it towards the end. As you head down the street there will be multiple seating areas on the left and right. When you get to the last one on the right, take the stairs down, then climb over the fence to access this area directly below the street.
The body is just over the fence on your right.

[size=4][b]Anti-piercing tactical media cargo pants[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] San Amaro St
[b]Location:[/b] Westbrook, Charter Hill
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from dead body on a platform with an billboard.

From San Amaro St fast travel, head north across the river and turn left. Follow the street until you get to the second street on the right and turn down it. You should see an billboard on the right.
Shoot the ladder to drop it down, so you can climb on it.

[size=4][b]Lightweight hardened-rubber media steel-toes[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Lele Park
[b]Location:[/b] Westbrook, Charter Hill
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a body on the roof of a fast-food restaurant.

Start from the Lele Park fast travel terminal, cross the street to The Rindo Hotel and head up the stairs to the right. Take the stairs on the left down to the seating area with the yellow umbrellas. The body is on the top of the food vendor. You can easily climb up using the umbrellas in front of the restaurant.
Potentially contains the pants as well as the shoes.
[/spoiler]

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Netrunner[/b][/color][/size]
[spoiler]
[size=4][b]Antisurge ICE-protected netrunner infovisor[/b][/size]
[b]Requirement:[/b] Reported Crime: Death from Above
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Abandoned Fuel Station
[b]Location:[/b] Badlands, Jackson Plains
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a metal container at the end of Reported Crime: Death from Above.

From Abandoned Fuel Station fast travel, head east along the road to find a burned car with a corpse. Loot it and read the shard to start the mission. The location is a little to the northwest from the fast travel terminal.
It's possible to get 2 of the Netrunner infovisors from the container.

[size=4][b]Heat-resistant hybridweave netrunning suit[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Ventura & Skyline
[b]Location:[/b] Heywood, Wellsprings
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a body in a small metal hut in The Glen, in Heywood.

Facing the Ventura & Skyline fast terminal, turn left and head down the road. Cross over the streat heading right and continue straight You will see a ramp leading into an alcove on your right. Directly ahead is a metal shack with big orange pipe going along on its right side. Go to the back of the shack and find the hole in the bottom.
Crouch to enter and head to the second room, where you will find a corpse with this item.

[size=4][b]Dura-membrane netrunner neotac pants[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Perishing Street
[b]Location:[/b] Watson, Northside
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a dead netrunner at the top of a water tower.

Facing The Perishing Street fast travel terminal, turn right and follow the street and take the next left up the ramp to the parking lot. On your right there are two identical water towers; you want the northern most one, behind the building. There will be a motorcycle at the bottom of the stairs.
Climb to the top to find the corpse with the loot.

[size=4][b]Hardened netrunner boots with composite inserts[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Luxury Apartments
[b]Location:[/b] Westbrook, Charter Hill
[b]Directions:[/b]
Found on a body inside a shaft in Charter Hill, Westbrook.

Facing the Luxury Apartments fast travel terminal turn right and head down the street. Take a right at the intersection. From there head south-west towards Lele St. When you get to the next intersection look diagonal left and cross over the street. There's an open hatch over the railings with another body just outside it.
Head inside the hatch and find the body with the loot.
[/spoiler]

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Nomad[/b][/color][/size]
[spoiler]
[size=4][b]Manganese-laminate nomad gas mask[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Solar Arrays
[b]Location:[/b] Badlands, Jackson Plains
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a metal box sitting on a sofa in an 'abandoned' camp.

From Solar Arrays fast travel, head south. The sofa is on the south side of a broken van in the middle of the camp.

[size=4][b]Duolayer microplate-mesh nomad jacket[/b][/size]
[b]Requirement:[/b] Body 20
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Border Checkpoint
[b]Location:[/b] Badlands, Jackson Plains
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a bunker outside an abandoned building.

From Border Checkpoint fast travel terminal, head due East-North-East. Cross over the road and keep heading East-North-East until you find an abandoned building the bunker is on the outside of the building with stairs leading down.
The item is inside the bunker.

[size=4][b]Polycarbonate nomad shirt with reinforced seams[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Tango Tors Motel
[b]Location:[/b] Badlands, Jackson Plains
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a body near a destroyed van.

From Tango Tors Motel fast travel, head south-west. The van is easy to spot from a distance. It's got white graffiti reading 'Reaper smiles upon you' on its left door.
On its south side you will find a corpse with the item.

[size=4][b]Ultralight tear-resistant nomad pants[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Las Palapas Motel
[b]Location:[/b] Badlands, Biotechnica Flats
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a body next to a crashed red van.

From Las Palapas Motel fast travel terminal, head north-east into the open fields. Look for a red van crashed head-first into a power pole.
There is a friendly drone next to the body, if you don't attack it, it will remain neutral, allowing you to easily loot the items.

[size=4][b]Durable bioleather nomad western boots[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Old Turbines
[b]Location:[/b] Badlands, Rocky Ridge
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted on a body inside a small underground bunker in the Badlands.

Head west-north-west from the Old Turbines Fast Travel terminal.
The bunker is just behind an abandoned gas station at the intersection.
[/spoiler]

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Rocker[/b][/color][/size]
[spoiler]
[size=4][b]Scratch-resistant polarized rocker aviators[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Almuneca & Jerez
[b]Location:[/b] Santo Domingo, Rancho Coronado
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a body next to the Foodscape store.

Facing the Almuneca & Jerez fast travel terminal, turn right and head down the street. Go past the first intersection and look for the Foodscape building on your left.
The body is on the north side of the building, below the Mallagra bridge, next to the concrete wall with the graffiti.

[size=4][b]Reinforced composite-lined rocker foldtop/Duolayer polyamide rocker vest[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Bellevue Overwalk
[b]Location:[/b] Watson, Kabuki
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a body in the middle of the catwalk area.

Facing the Bellevue Overwalk fast travel terminal, climb the staircase to the left.
The body is in the middle of the catwalk.

[size=4][b]Armorweave rocker bra/Reinforced-seam cotton rocker tank[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Batty's Hotel
[b]Location:[/b] Pacifica, Coastview
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a body on a destroyed concert mini stage.

From the Batty's Hotel fast travel terminal, head north-east out of the driveway and turn left onto the street. Just past the billboards on your right, near the Rio Benito street sign, is a broken railing. Climb up there and follow the balcon until you get to the destroyed concert mini stage.
The body containging the item is the left one on the stage, near the guitars.

[size=4][b]Elastic flame-resistant rocker pants[/b][/size]
[b]Requirement:[/b] Body 15
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Downtown North
[b]Location:[/b] City Center, Downtown
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a body inside a metal cage.

From Downtown North fast travel, head west along Bruce Skiv street. Walk under the megabuilding and right after it you will see the big metal cage up and to your left. The body containing this item is inside the cage.
You can enter the cage from the top to bypass the body check.

[size=4][b]Puncture-resistant rocker ankle boots[/b][/size]
[b]Requirement:[/b] Body 15
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Skyline & Republic
[b]Location:[/b] City Center, Downtown
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a cage at the end of an alley.

From Skyline & Republic fast travel, head directly east and follow the street to the next crossroad, then turn north (left). Turn left at the Bruce Skiv street sign and go up the stairs. The cage with the body is at the end of this alley.
You can also reach the area through a hole in the fence on the north side, facing the water to bypass the body check.
[/spoiler]

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Solo[/b][/color][/size]
[spoiler]
[size=4][b]Titanium solo techgogs with tactical software[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Protein Farm
[b]Location:[/b] Badlands, Biotechnica Flats
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a dead body in the shipping landmass.

From Protein Farm fast travel, head east (or west from Fuel Station).
The body is at a blocked off T-intersection halfway between the two fast travel terminals on the map.

[size=4][b]Heavy shock-absorbent solo jacket[/b][/size]
[b]Requirement:[/b] Technical 20
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Senate & Market
[b]Location:[/b] Heywood, The Glen
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a small caged area.

From Senate & Market fast travel terminal, cross the road and head east past the Time Machine music shop. Keep following the road east to towards Megabuilding 01. On the right side of Megabuilding 01, there is an alley with a metal cage on the left. The only entrance is through the door. You need 20 Technical to open the door.
As you enter, keep walking to the other end of the cage, the body will be on your left.

[size=4][b]Ultrathin composite-print solo shirt[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Old Turbines
[b]Location:[/b] Badlands, Jackson Plains
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a suitcase next to a small rock formation.

From the Old Turbines fast travel terminal, head east-north-east. Cross over the road and continue until you see a small rock formation with some bodies and look scattered around.
The item is in the suitcase

[size=4][b]Armor-plated syn-leather solo pants[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Pumping Station
[b]Location:[/b] Heywood, Wellsprings
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a body in a shack in an alcove on the beach.

From Pumping Station fast travel, head west until you reach the end of the street. Enter the balcony area through the open gate. Follow that around to the left and you should find a lader on your right. Take that down to the beach. Immediatly turn left and walk south keeping an eye on your left for a green metal fence. Through the fence is a shack, jump over it to find the entrance.
The body with the pants is inside that shack on a corpse of an Animal gang member NPC.

[size=4][b]Gold-tipped manganese steel solo boots[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Kabuki
[b]Location:[/b] Watson, Kabuki
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a metal container behind a cook.

From Kabuki fast travel terminal, head south-west and cross the road. You should see an entrance with stairs leading down to the markets. Turn left after the stairs and take the elevator to the 3rd floor.
The container is behind the cook.
[/spoiler]

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Techie[/b][/color][/size]
[spoiler]
[size=4][b]Cushioned techie baseball cap[/b][/size]
[b]Requirement:[/b] Technical 15
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Rocky Ridge
[b]Location:[/b] Badlands, Rocky Ridge
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a metal box in a basement under a house.

From Rocky Ridge fast travel, head towards the fuel station. Take the road inbetween the bar and the fuel station. Turn right at the intersection and contiune on past the next intersection. The house is the first on on the left. Behind the house you will find the basement entrance.
The item is inside a metal box with an Arasaka label on it, on a shelf to your left from the entrance.

[size=4][b]Laminated ICE-protected techie ocuset[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Edgewood Farm
[b]Location:[/b] Badlands, Rocky Ridge
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a metal container inside a burned down trailer.

From Edgewood Farm Fast Travel terminal, go west until you see the trailer.
Look for the Fuyutshki Electronics container inside the trailer.

[size=4][b]Polycarbonate nanoweave techie harness[/b][/size]
[b]Requirement:[/b] Body 20
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Venture & Skyline
[b]Location:[/b] Heywood, The Glen
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a metal box inside a storage container.

From Venture & Skyline fast travel terminal, head west down the street. When you get to the intersection, turn left and go up the ramp. Go straight a head until you see a storage shed with  Valentinos graffiti. The storage shed we want is just to the right of it. There is a red light that will be your clue for which door to open.
Once inside, open the metal box on the counter.

[size=4][b]Thermoactive tear-resistant techie shirt[/b][/size]
[b]Requirement:[/b] Complete 'Ghost Town' mission, reach 34 Street Cred, and wait 2 days
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Rocky Ridge
[b]Location:[/b] Badlands, Red Peaks
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a container in the tunnel with the Murkmobile.

From Rocky Ridge fast travel, head to the tunnel location associated with the 'Ghost Town' mission (Murk Man location).
The item is inside a container behind the Murkmobile.

[size=4][b]Reinforced duolayer techie cargo pants[/b][/size]
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Dam Viewpoint
[b]Location:[/b] Santo Domingo, Rancho Coronado
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a corpse near two police cars.

From Dam Viewpoint fast travel terminal, follow the road to the right to go down. Keep following the road after you pass through the tunnel. Straight ahead is an incident on the side of the road with two police cars nearby.
The body is next to the truck.

[size=4][b]Cushioned aramid-sole techie shoes[/b][/size]
[b]Requirement:[/b] Technical 15
[b]Fast Travel:[/b] Metro: Memorial Park
[b]Location:[/b] City Center, Corpo Plaza
[b]Directions:[/b]
Looted from a dead technician behind a gate in Corpo Plaza.

From Metro: Memorial Park head up the stairs to the ring road and turn right. Follow it around to the Militech HQ Building. To the right of the AV landing pads is a gate leading to the dead technician.
If you time it and position it right, you can double jump twice to make it over the top of the fence bypassing the check to open the gate.
[/spoiler]

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]V's Set[/b][/color][/size]
[spoiler]
[size=4][b]V's favorite top/T-shirt[/b][/size]
[b]Directions:[/b]
Granted automtically to you when starting 'The Rescue' main job

[size=4][b]V's pants[/b][/size]
[b]Directions:[/b]
Granted automtically to you when starting 'The Rescue' main job

[size=4][b]V's sneakers[/b][/size]
[b]Directions:[/b]
Granted automtically to you when starting 'The Rescue' main job
[/spoiler]

[line]
[size=5][color=#ffff00][b]Yorinobu[/b][/color][/size]
[spoiler]
[size=4][b]Kotetsu no Ryu coat[/b][/size]
[b]Requirement:[/b] Only available during the Heist
[b]Location:[/b] Watson, Arasaka Waterfront
[b]Directions:[/b]
Can be found inside a cache in the bathroom of Yorinobu's Penthouse in Konpeki Plaza during The Heist.

[size=4][b]Yorinobu's formal shirt[/b][/size]
[b]Requirement:[/b] Only available during the Heist
[b]Location:[/b] Watson, Arasaka Waterfront
[b]Directions:[/b]
Can be found inside a cache in Yorinobu's Penthouse in Konpeki Plaza during The Heist.

[size=4][b]Yorinobu's slacks[/b][/size]
[b]Requirement:[/b] Only available during the Heist
[b]Location:[/b] Watson, Arasaka Waterfront
[b]Directions:[/b]
Can be found inside a cache in Yorinobu's Penthouse in Konpeki Plaza during The Heist.
[/spoiler]

[line]
